The McCord Museum is the museum of all Montrealers, a social history museum that celebrates life in Montreal, both 
past and presentits history, its people, and its communities. Open to the city and the world, the Museum presents 
exciting exhibitions, educational programming and cultural activities that offer a contemporary perspective on history, 
engaging visitors from Montreal, Canada and beyond. It is home to one of the largest historical collections in North 
America comprising over 200,000 objects and works of art, 2.15 million photographs, 3,500 rare books and 340 linear 
metres of textual archives, hat make up in its Dress, Fashion and Textiles, Photography, Indigenous Cultures, 
Documentary Art, Material Culture, and Archives collections. McCord Museum: Our People, Our Stories. All of the 
McCord Museums activities revolve around six core values: rigour, integrity, inclusion, audacity, creativity and 
commitment. 
We are seeking an  Admission and boutique attendant 
Reference No: 202211E   
Reporting to the head, Visitor service, your principle duties will include: 
Reception and ticket sale functions: 
Greet visitors with courtesy and process tickets. Operate a computerized point of sale (POS) and 
inventory system; 
Provide the public with information about the Museum and on regional tourism (in person and by 
telephone); 
Prepare and distribute useful additions for exhibitions (audio-guides, adventure bags, iPad, iPod, etc); 
Promote museum membership, exhibitions and museum activities; 
Record attendance, passes, memberships, museum cards and various discounts; 
Prepare bank deposits and balance cash daily; 
Look after the general appearance of the entrance area; 
Fill displays with museum brochures; 
Answer the phone, take messages and follow up on the phone and e-mail; 
Ensure the follow-up on photo orders; 
Occasionally host events (welcoming guests, coat check); 
Act as a resource person for the operation of the multimedia Theatre (use of a microphone). 
 Boutique : 
Provide an excellent and bilingual customer service and process sales of goods; 
Advise customers and develop sales of products; 
Process online sales and special orders; 
Maintain merchandise displays and product facing; 
Carry out inventory functions: receiving, labelling and display of products; 
Maintain an observant eye over the store to minimize theft; 
Maintain general appearance of the shop (may involve some light cleaning duties).  
Employment conditions 
Part-time unionized position. 20 hours of availability per week to be given; 
Variable hours of work, including weekends and certain evenings; 11.5 guaranteed hours; 
Entry position hourly rate: $16.01; 
Start Date: as soon as possible.   Qualifications and profile required 
Collegial diploma; 
Fluency in English and French; knowledge of a third language would be an asset; 
One (1) year of retail experience, operating computerized cash register and handling sales; 
Welcoming, courteous and helpful disposition, excellent customer service; 
Honesty and sense of responsibility; 
Well-groomed appearance and wearing the museum uniform; 
Skills in merchandising and gift-wrapping; 
Interest for the cultural and tourist environment, as well as Indigenous and Canadian arts and crafts. 

The McCord Museum is committed to providing a skilled workforce that reflects the diversity of Montreal's population. We hire  based on individual role requirements and select our employees based on their qualifications, skills and experience. We do  not discriminate based on personal differences.  
