Company Description
Ubisofts 20,000 team members, working across more than 30 countries around the world, are bound by a common mission to enrich players lives with original and memorable gaming experiences. Their commitment and talent have brought to life many acclaimed franchises such as Assassins Creed, Far Cry, Watch Dogs, Just Dance, Rainbow Six, and many more to come. Ubisoft is an equal opportunity employer that believes diverse backgrounds and perspectives are key to creating worlds where both players and teams can thrive and express themselves. If you are excited about solving game-changing challenges, cutting edge technologies and pushing the boundaries of entertainment, we invite you to join our journey and help us create the unknown. 

Job Description
You will be part of the MDM (Master Data Management) team within the UDO (Ubisoft Data Office) organization responsible for enterprise-wide data governance.
MDM (Master data management) is the discipline that ensures a global, reliable and quality view of business data. At the center of the company's cross-functional processes and business analysis, the MDM enables decisions to be made at the heart of the data. This discipline is a natural extension of distributed architectures designed to facilitate the sharing and exchange of information.
As a Business Analyst, you will be in charge of MDM topics addressed in one or more international IT projects.
Responsibilities
Lead the scoping studies upstream of the design and implementation phases: identification and formalization of business processes and management rules for internal customers (marketing, finance, sales, supply chain, or others);
Gather and understand the business needs as well as their challenges;
Write functional specifications based on a 360 analysis of the use of data typologies (Products, Internal Organization, Markets, Customers and others);
Accompany the configuration of the chosen solution in collaboration with the development teams;
Lead the monitoring of requirements with the development teams to ensure quality and consistency between the business expectations and the delivered products;
Lead and participate in the integration testing, training and user acceptance phases;
Collaborate with other IT teams in a pro-active manner to implement necessary changes and evolutions;
Be in charge of change management projects in collaboration with the business and IT teams;
Support the management of the project activity: definition of the planning, monitoring of deadlines, review of deliverables, quality of documentation and monitoring of developments. 

Qualifications

Proven work experience in Master Data Management;
Experience working with different IT project development methodologies;
Organizational skills and ability to coordinate different stakeholders;
Experience with EBX or a competing solution (Informatica);
Ability to analyze, model and translate business issues;
Ability to communicate with both business and technical teams.
Additional Information
Just a heads up: If you require a work permit, your eligibility may depend on your education and years of relevant work experience, as required by the government.
Skills and competencies show up in different forms and can be based on different experiences, that's why we strongly encourage you to apply even though you may not have all the requirements listed above.
At Ubisoft, you can come as you are. We embrace diversity in all its forms. Were committed to fostering a work environment that is inclusive and respectful of all differences.

